<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="572" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1377,1834]" box="[151,806,1377,1402]" pageId="5" pageNumber="572">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1377,1402]" pageId="5" pageNumber="572">Description.</emphasis>
Length (including wings): male 
<quantity box="[664,802,1378,1402]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.35" metricValueMax="4.4" metricValueMin="4.3" pageId="5" pageNumber="572" unit="mm" value="4.35" valueMax="4.4" valueMin="4.3">4.3–4.4 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1377,1834]" pageId="5" pageNumber="572">
Crown yellowish, with brownish markings. Face stramineous, with brownish and black markings; lateral and base margin of anteclypeus black, apical region brown; base of antenna black (
<figureCitation box="[1057,1123,1449,1474]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1932,1954]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,210,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,191,1910]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Chileanoscopus serrulatus sp. nov. A, habitus of male, dorsal view; B, habitus of male, lateral view; C, face of male; D, face of female; E, forewing; F, habitus of female, dorsal view; G, habitus of female, lateral view; H, first valvulae; I, second valvulae; J, female abdomen, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/344765/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="572">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
C). Female color similar to male, except face without more black markings (
<figureCitation box="[697,761,1485,1510]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1932,1954]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,210,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,191,1910]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Chileanoscopus serrulatus sp. nov. A, habitus of male, dorsal view; B, habitus of male, lateral view; C, face of male; D, face of female; E, forewing; F, habitus of female, dorsal view; G, habitus of female, lateral view; H, first valvulae; I, second valvulae; J, female abdomen, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/344765/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="572">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
D).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1377,1834]" box="[199,1147,1521,1546]" pageId="5" pageNumber="572">
Male abdomen with tergal apodemes broad, longer than one segment long (
<figureCitation box="[1043,1110,1521,1546]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1715,1737]" captionTargetBox="[168,1397,207,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,191,1692]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Chileanoscopus serrulatus sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal segments, and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, connective, ventral view; C, connective, lateral view; D, abdominal segment II and apodemes; E, aedeagus, lateral view; F, aedeagus, ventral view; G, style, lateroventral view; H, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/344767/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="572">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
D).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1377,1834]" pageId="5" pageNumber="572">
Male genital. Style lateral lobe rounded, without hook or pointed (
<figureCitation box="[974,1043,1557,1582]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1715,1737]" captionTargetBox="[168,1397,207,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,191,1692]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Chileanoscopus serrulatus sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal segments, and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, connective, ventral view; C, connective, lateral view; D, abdominal segment II and apodemes; E, aedeagus, lateral view; F, aedeagus, ventral view; G, style, lateroventral view; H, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/344767/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="572">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
G). Aedeagal shaft slightly broad, obviously curved dorsally, nearly beyond dorsal apodeme, surface with irregularly serrate (
<figureCitation box="[1170,1247,1593,1618]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1715,1737]" captionTargetBox="[168,1397,207,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,191,1692]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Chileanoscopus serrulatus sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal segments, and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, connective, ventral view; C, connective, lateral view; D, abdominal segment II and apodemes; E, aedeagus, lateral view; F, aedeagus, ventral view; G, style, lateroventral view; H, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/344767/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="572">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
E–F).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
