<subSubSection box="[199,1126,1701,1726]" pageId="5" pageNumber="572" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1377,1834]" box="[199,1126,1701,1726]" pageId="5" pageNumber="572">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1701,1726]" pageId="5" pageNumber="572">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet refers to the serrate margins of the aedeagal shaft.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="572" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1377,1834]" pageId="5" pageNumber="572">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1737,1762]" pageId="5" pageNumber="572">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Heller, 1969" authorityName="Heller" authorityYear="1969" box="[665,953,1737,1762]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Chileanoscopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hichinsi">
<emphasis box="[665,788,1737,1761]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="572">C. hichinsi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Heller" box="[803,945,1737,1762]" pageId="5" pageNumber="572" refString="Heller, F. (1969) Eine neue Idioceridae aus Chile: Idiocerus hichinsi n. sp. (Homoptera). Entomologische Zeitschrift Frankfurt a M, 79, 155 - 157." type="journal article" year="1969">Heller, 1969</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in body color, but can be distinguished by the serrate aedeagal shaft that is obviously curved dorsally, and the male tergal apodemes slightly longer than the length of one segment.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
